postcontent:
PSA upper/lower with Foliage Green Magpul furniture (now a discontinued color). 16" heavy profile 1:7 twist rate, mid length gas tube, chrome lined, cold hammer forged, and made by FN. Rifle has a PSA full auto BCG, PSA lower parts kit, standard A2 hider, MOE mid length hand guard with magpul VFG, rear MBUIS, Mil-dot Leapers scope (cheap but holds zero), MOE stock/pistol grip, and a backplate with sling attachment. Chambered in 5.56 Nato, so no worries about shooting .223 from this rifle.

Comes with 4 foliage green Pmags, 2 aluminum mags, Flat Dark Earth (FDE) Magpul MOE stock, FDE Magpul MOE grip, and FED Magpul trigger guard, ~100 stripper clips w/feed lips, 2 DPMS accurizing wedge's, castle nut wrench, and a standard backing plate. This is a complete sell/trade and I will not part this out.

Rifle has had roughly 500 rounds through it. Some marks on the barrel finish from being stored on a rack and a small mark near the bolt release pin. The heavy barrel and mid length gas tube make this a nice shooter. Less recoil and jump than a carbine length gas tube.

Buyer must be willing to sign a bill of sale and present VALID AL drivers license and/or conceal carry license.

title: For Sale:  2 Piston ARs - PWS MK116 & MK114
postcontent:
I have 2 piston driven ARs for sale..both are phenomenal rifles, both in excellent shape.
If you are not familiar with them, do yourself a favor and research them.  
PWS makes the best piston system on the market, hands down.  Only piston AR out there with long stroke modeled after the venerable AK47, all other pistons out there today are short stroke and require more proprietary parts which are more prone to failure as all of these short stroke systems utilize metal on metal action, where as the long stroke does not have metal on metal contact.  System is super reliable.  Another great part to add is that the PWS mod 0 and mod 1 both weigh less than 7 lbs! so you're getting a ultra reliable piston driven AR with the weight of a traditional DI gun.  

These guns are dreams to shoot..I wouldn't be selling them if I didn't need the money.

PWS MK116 Mod 0 chambered in 556---$1500 OBO, cost $1750 BNIB

can send pics if interested, haven't had time to take pics / upload but will plan on doing so in next few days hopefully.

Up for sale is a 5.45x39 Saiga. I had planned on this being my "go to" rifle for the future and is set up as such.  I jut got bit by the .308 bug instead. This rifle has had about 500 rounds of NON corrosive only ran though it.

 It has been converted back from sporter to military form. It has a correct  Russian 90* gas block and bayonet lug; both of those things are Russian AK74 milspec and most Saiga conversions don't have this. It also has an Echo 93V3/QD sling mount and Polish Beryl milspec railed hand-guard with vertical foregrip. The hand-guard is Polish MilSpec made of high impact polymer with a aluminum heat shield, great for mounting a tac light to your ak without clamping it to the barrel. It also has a Russian chrome lined muzzle brake, not some off center Tapco paper weight. It does not have the muzzle brake pin, but that is a easy to find $5 part available from APEX or KVAR.  It also has a Tapco G2 trigger.

It also comes with 9 Milspec mags, 5 Bulgarian steel reinforced Circle 10 black mags, 1 TAN Bulgarian Circle 21 mag, and 3 Polish Tantal mags that were re-coated by the  importer. Again, these are NOT American junk mags, these are all top quality MilSpec mags.

Also includes a BCS industries 5 cell Molle chest rig in ATACS FG with upgraded harness. This is a VERY heavy duty chest rig that will take much abuse.

Also included is an ammo can full of BANNED surplus 7N6 5.45x39 Soviet surplus. A little over 1,000 rounds. If I get a serious inquiry I will make a definite count.  

This rifle AND this ammo is BANNED by our........"great leader"....And NO MORE will be imported. I have the original inspection paperwork from the Izhmash factory.

Will take $1,5000 cash, or trade for semi auto .308's (with cash towards me or you, depending on the trade). HK91's, PTR's, M1A's, GOOD FALs's.

If you see anything in the pics that doesn't look right, it's a problem with the picture, not the rifle.  I chose through a handful of those Gold Medallions and picked this one and then sent the stock off to a custom stock maker in MO to have the shiny Browning stuff stripped off and a nice hand-rubbed finish applied.  I remember that being about $400 alone.  I have a very nice illuminated reticle Swarovski scope on it now that isn't included, but can be purchased for an additional $1250.  I have the box, a Browning sling and a nice Browning soft case.  I also have a nice synthetic stock with a Decelerator recoil pad for hunting so you don't scratch that beautiful wood.  It has the BOSS system, and I have the conventional recoil attachment so you can choose to use the brake at the range and the CR attachment while hunting.  It's a shooter and when I use to shoot it a few years back I remember it being MOA or close to it with a few different ammo types.  I haven't shot it in years and I'm cleaning out my safe and working on rearranging a few things.  Check out my other listings and load up your safe with some nice weapons!

Here is a list of states that honor an Illinois non-resident CCW permits. (Nonresident 19 states, Resident 20 states as of July 2014)

Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, Idaho, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Kentucky, Mississippi, Missouri, North Carolina, Oklahoma, South Dakota, Tennessee, Utah, Vermont, Wisconsin.

And if you are an Illinois resident you can add Michigan to that list.

Am I Eligible for a Concealed Carry License?

 ILLINOIS RESIDENTS
â¾I am at least 21 years old.
â¾I have a valid Firearm Owner's Identification card. Or applied for. (FOID Card)
â¾I have not been convicted or found guilty of a misdemeanor involving the threat of physical force or violence to any person within the past 5 years.
â¾I do not have 2 or more violations related to driving while under the influence of alcohol, other drugs, intoxicating compounds within the past 5 years.
â¾I am not subject to a pending arrest warrant, prosecution or proceeding for an offense or action that could lead to disqualification to own or possess a firearm.
â¾I have not been in a residential or court-ordered treatment for alcoholism, alcohol detoxification, or drug treatment within the past 5 years.
â¾You may be eligible if you satisfy the above and no objections are filed by law enforcement.

 NON-RESIDENTS - Am I Eligible for an Illinois Concealed Carry License?
â¾Must meet all the above requirements except for the FOID card, plus the following;
â¾Be a resident of one of the following states; Hawaii, New Mexico, South Carolina or Virgin.
â¾Have a permit from your state of residency.

This is a 2-day class, 8 hours each day including range qualification.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Model 27 .357 Magnum Revolver 357          The Original, NIB, Highly Sought After
postcontent:
Smith & Wesson Model 27 357 Magnum with an 8 3/8" pinned barrel. It comes in a wooden display box and has all the paperwork. It has a "Nickel Finish" and looks amazing. The Smith & Wesson Model 27 is the original .357 Magnum revolver and was first produced in 1935, and many versions of it are still in production today. The Model 27 was built on Smith & Wesson's carbon steel, large N-frame, and was available at various times with 3 1/2", 4", 5", 6" or 8 3/8" barrel lengths and had adjustable sights. When first introduced by Smith & Wesson in 1935 it was known as the Registered Magnum. The model was essentially a custom order revolver. Barrel lengths could be had in quarter-inch increments from 3.5" to 8.75" in length. In addition to the different lengths of barrels available there were different grips, front sights, triggers, hammers, and finishes available. Each Registered Magnum came with a certificate of authenticity. Even though it was introduced in the middle of the Great Depression and was extremely expensive, Smith & Wesson found itself backlogged with orders for the four years that it produced the Registered Magnum. The Kansas City Police Department issued the Registered Magnum to its officers, and many other law enforcement officers across the United States carried the Registered Magnum. In 1939 Smith & Wesson stopped producing the Registered Magnum. It was replaced with the .357 Magnum. 
Email....REDACTED
